 So the function's name is actually called party,

00:02:37.640 --> 00:02:38.920
 but it just happens to be called party

00:02:38.920 --> 00:02:40.840
 because we're storing the function's code

00:02:40.840 --> 00:02:44.260
 in a instance variable called party.

00:02:44.260 --> 00:02:46.080
 But that's how we're gonna call it.

00:02:46.080 --> 00:02:48.160
 So in the party variable,

00:02:48.160 --> 00:02:51.400
 we have the code that is those two lines.

00:02:51.400 --> 00:02:53.760
 And then within that method,

00:02:53.760 --> 00:02:57.240
 now I'd call party a method to use the terminology.

00:02:57.240 --> 00:02:59.040
 Within the party method,

00:02:59.040 --> 00:03:02.080
 this is the instance that we're talking about.

