 and this got set to zero.

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:26.120
 So when we're at this next line of code,

00:05:26.120 --> 00:05:29.040
 before we call an.party for the first time,

00:05:29.040 --> 00:05:31.480
 an.x has got a zero in it.

00:05:31.480 --> 00:05:36.120
 Then we call an.party, and it runs the code an.party.

00:05:36.120 --> 00:05:40.120
 This an is an alias for this.

00:05:40.120 --> 00:05:42.640
 And so in a sense, when it says this.x,

00:05:42.640 --> 00:05:44.600
 it really is an.x.

00:05:44.600 --> 00:05:47.440
 Now we'll see in a second how, when we do multiple instances,

