 and we make the thing.

00:06:24.880 --> 00:06:29.840
 So I mentioned the word constructor,

00:06:29.840 --> 00:06:33.320
 'cause there is this moment where it's actually building

00:06:33.320 --> 00:06:36.400
 the object and filling it up with all the little pieces.

00:06:36.400 --> 00:06:41.400
 So objects are created, used by us, and then discarded.

00:06:41.400 --> 00:06:44.240
 And there is this concept of a bit of code

00:06:44.240 --> 00:06:47.160
 called the constructor in object-oriented theory

00:06:47.160 --> 00:06:49.640
 that says, look, I'm gonna start an empty object,

00:06:49.640 --> 00:06:51.100
 and then I'll fill it with stuff.

00:06:51.100 --> 00:06:53.160
 And the constructor is the sort of filling it up

00:06:53.160 --> 00:06:55.200
 so it's ready to do its job

00:06:55.200 --> 00:06:56.940
 once you're done constructing it.

00:06:56.940 --> 00:06:58.640
 Destructors are a common concept,

