 You don't get to get ahold of the destructor

00:07:04.440 --> 00:07:05.600
 inside of JavaScript.

00:07:05.600 --> 00:07:08.720
 That's something that they just don't let you do.

00:07:08.720 --> 00:07:11.680
 And I think it philosophically has to do with the idea

00:07:11.680 --> 00:07:13.720
 that you're in a webpage, you're not gonna be there

