 for very long, and that's really the earliest of days, right?

00:07:17.120 --> 00:07:19.560
 These days, with things like Vue and React,

00:07:19.560 --> 00:07:22.320
 some of these JavaScript pages last a very long time,

00:07:22.320 --> 00:07:25.160
 and maybe it'd be useful to have destructors in there,

00:07:25.160 --> 00:07:27.560
 but JavaScript didn't have them in the beginning.

00:07:27.560 --> 00:07:31.760
 Okay, so the constructor is, in a sense,

00:07:31.760 --> 00:07:34.880
 the moment where we are this new

